{
  "texts": [
    "The total temperature profile was calculated from temperature profiles of the solid and liquid regions as density-weighted averages:",
    "The temperature jump 𝛥𝑇 was then obtained as the difference between the extrapolated linear fits of the solid and liquid temperature curves at the interface position 𝑧 𝑒𝑞.",
    "The example of temperature distribution with temperature jumps is shown in Figure 4: To accurately determine 𝑧 𝑒𝑞, we used the density profile 𝜌(𝑧) and applied the concept of the Gibbs dividing surface 43, 97, which defines the interface as the position that balances the excess density on both sides.",
    "This condition is expressed as:",
    "where 𝜌 1 and 𝜌 2 are the bulk densities of both phases."
  ]
}